I"ô<p><a href="https://www.postgresql.org">PostgreSQL</a> is a <strong>fast</strong>, <strong>reliable</strong> and <strong>open source</strong>(free) <a href="https://database.guide/what-is-an-ordbms">object-relational database management system</a> (<em>it stores data in relations: which are really just tables with rows and columns</em>). It can hold databases as large as 32TB, with virtually unlimited rows. This makes it an ideal choice for many companies dealing with large volumes of data.</p>
